This paper is about medical relation extraction using a graph neural network to represent dependency forests. The task involves natural language processing and machine learning, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of graph neural networks also suggests the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the task of relation extraction involves information retrieval and text mining, which could fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
